Name: Bandit
Description: Your Kamigotchi becomes quick and decisive. They strike fast and retreat before their enemy has a chance to react.

Name: Aggression
Description: Your Kami starts snapping at the competition. But they're bound to turn on you, so take them out before they do.

Name: Sniper
Description: Attacks exhausts a Kamigotchi's energy. There's no rest for the wicked and Snipers usually act quickly enough for you to claim the bounty they collected, before the enemy has time to organise.

Name: Warmonger
Description: Kami are territorial and Warmongers fiercely so. Honing them in battle will make them nearly unstoppable. Just don't let anyone get the jump on you.

Name: Protector
Description: Your Kamigotchis spiritual connection to the land deepens, letting them stave off foes while harvesting.

Name: Endurance
Description: Lets your Kamigotchi stick around a node for longer, and makes it harder for enemies to steal away their hard-earned MUSU.

Name: Defensiveness
Description: Helps Kamigotchi who wanna be left alone to harvest. It grants them a calming aura which deters the attacks of violent Kamigotchi.

Name: Patience
Description: Your Kami gains access to a Zen-like state where they're increasingly impervious to the strains of harvesting. They might still be awake after a long night, when your day dawns.

Name: Greed
Description: Your Kamigotchi harvests every little scrap of MUSU without missing a beat. Undeterred by the cries of the competing Kamigotchi they shove aside to get it.

Name: Acquisitiveness
Description: MUSU is strangely addictive and your Kamigotchi's desire for it pushes them to harvest more. Hopefully you'll never run out again.

Name: Sunglasses Ownership
Description: With a pair of nifty sunglasses your Kamigotchi will still be standing when others lie face down in the mud from exhaustion.

Name: Leverage
Description: Your Kamigotchi learns the ins and outs of nodes. Whether in scrap or in forests, they become skilled in using the surroundings to their advantage.

Name: Looping
Description: Studying your Kamigotchi's movement you'd think they'd gone mad. But there's undeniably a method to it. Look away for a few minutes and you'll already have enough MUSU for a snack.
